<section id="fb0">
	<p align="left"><b>For</b></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">2: More people visit museums</font></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">3: National heritage and culture is accessible to everyone</font></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">6: Museums are less commercial/more serious</font></p><p align="left"></p><p align="left"><b>Against</b></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">1: Museums may be overcrowded</font></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">4: Museums lack financial resources</font></p><p align="left"><font color="#000000">5: Museums are less independent/more subject to government policy</font></p>
</section>
<section id="rt2001">
	<p align="left">This writing task asks about the 'benefits' and 'drawbacks' of a situation, which is the same as asking about its advantages and disadvantages. Before you do this exercise, spend a few minutes noting down what you think the advantages and disadvantages of free admission to museums are. Then, after you have done the exercise, compare your ideas with the ones mentioned by the people.</p>
